<edge source="World Athletics Federation" target="Noah Carter">
  <data key="d7">79.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Noah Carter, an athlete, achieved a significant milestone in his career when he set a new 100-meter (100m) sprint record. This remarkable feat was officially recognized and validated by the World Athletics Federation. The validation process involved confirming that Noah Carter's performance met all necessary criteria for setting a new record.

The World Athletics Federation played a crucial role in this achievement, ensuring that the record was set under fair conditions and adhering to established guidelines. The federation's validation of Noah Carter’s 100m sprint record underscores the significance of his accomplishment within the athletics community. This recognition not only highlights Noah Carter's exceptional talent but also reinforces the World Athletics Federation's commitment to maintaining high standards in athletic competitions.

The new 100m sprint record was set during a championship event, adding to its prestige and importance. The validation by the World Athletics Federation further solidifies this achievement as an official part of athletics history.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation validates Noah Carter's new 100m sprint record set at the championship.</data>
